<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727548>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Life coloration of Amnirana parva sp. nov.; (a) male holotype (ZMB 88458) and (b) female paratype (ZMB 88438); b from the type locality, the Krahn-Bassa Proposed Protected Forest in eastern Liberia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727546>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Preserved holotype of Amnirana parva sp. nov. (ZMB 88458) in dorsal (a), ventral (b), and lateral view (c), as well as ventral views of left hand (d), and foot (e); scale bars= 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727546/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727550>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Adult paratypes of Amnirana parva sp. nov.; (a) male (ZMB 87110, found without left hand), and (b) female (ZMB 87111) from Mount Ghi, Liberia, shown to illustrate sexual size dimorphism, as well as differences in dorsal coloration, and skin texture; scale bar= 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727550/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727552>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Life coloration of Amnirana parva sp. nov.; (a), (b) & (f) males from Foya Proposed Protected Area, Liberia; (c) male and (d) tadpole from Taï National Park, Ivory Coast; (e) couple from Déré Classified Forest, Guinea; (g) female from Banco National Park, Ivory Coast; (h) male from Gola Rainforest National Park, Sierra Leone; specimens not retained as vouchers; further specimens from the Foya Proposed Protected Area and the Gola Rainforest National Park have been DNA-barcoded, the species identity of frogs from the other sites is presumed based on their morphological appearance and their occurrence in primary, lowland evergreen rainforest (compare text)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727560>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Habitats and life-history images of Amnirana parva sp. nov. from Ivory Coast; (a) & (b) artificial fish breeding ponds in the Banco National Park; (c) A. parva sp. nov. female, perched on palm leaf in the Tanoé forest reserve, with a blood sucking fly on the snout; (d) clutch (Banco National Park), (e) large tadpole (Azagny National Park), and (f) juvenile of Amnirana parva sp. nov. (Banco National Park); (g) A. parva sp. nov. male (Azagny National Park)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727560/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727544>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Advertisement calls of (a) Amnirana ‘albolabris West’ and (b) A. fonensis; shown are oscillogram (top) und spectrogram (bottom; please note different scale of y-axes in a and b)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727544/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727556>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Geographic records of the examined Amnirana parva sp. nov. (circles) and A. fonensis (triangles) specimens in the Upper Guinea Forest Zone (inset: its position on the African continent). The two type localities are marked by black symbols. From south to north colors indicate a gradient from lowland rainforests, via forest-savanna mosaics into ever drier savanna ecosystems and the Sahara Desert in the far north. Dark green colors in the south indicate primary rainforest, the olive-green color in that vegetation zone indicates degraded or converted former rainforest (modified after Arino 2012)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727556/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7727558>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Habitats and eggs of Amnirana parva sp. nov.; (a) & (b) small forest streams in the Krahn-Bassa Proposed Protected Area, Liberia, the type locality of the new species; (c) & (d) forest streams in Gola Rainforest National Park, Sierra Leone; (e) developing A. parva sp. nov. embryos in the Gola Rainforest National Park." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7727558/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

